  "texts": [
    "Secondly, the fill factor (FF), indicating a solar cell's effectiveness in converting sunlight into electricity, is also impacted by temperature.",
    "Higher temperatures tend to diminish FF due to increased resistive losses within the cell, resulting in an overall efficiency decrease (Elbar et al., 2019; Lakhdar & Hima, 2020).",
    "Illustrated in Fig. 4 is the correlation between solar cell efficiency and temperature.",
    "As temperature rises, efficiency experiences a decline attributed Fig. 3 Efficiency landscape: a comparative overview of solar cell generations and active materials (Saha et al., 2015) to heightened electron-hole recombination rates and alterations in the bandgap properties of materials.",
    "This awareness of temperature-dependent behavior is pivotal for optimizing solar cell performance and implementing effective cooling strategies (Ouédraogo et al., 2021)."
  ]
}